channel.title: Garbage Collection
channel.description:
@ Server.java Find: [code]private static void debug() {[/code]
Under there you should see something like: [code]System.gc();[/code]
Remove it and compile re-run
You should see fairly good improvement on your engine load and cycle Time
How do i know?
Well i added that a few days ago and noticed my Engine Load went from 0.30% Engine load Up to Atleast 10% with only 1 player online and cycle Time of 50Ms from 5ms I then couldn't figure out what was causing it so i thought i must have an memory Leak then remembered i added that method so i removed it and it went back to normal so i thought i May aswell release this just incase this could be causing other peoples servers to be unstable also.
Hate i don't really care tbh just contributing.
